headline.main: NEW-YORK CITY.; Society Library--Blection of Trustees. Commissioners of Emigration. Farmers' Club, American Institute. A Strike on the Sixth-avenue Railroad. Encouraging to Distant Friends. Fillbusters, Slavers, &c., Look Out. Fire in Pearl-street. THE POLICE COMMISSIONERS. Trouble between the Mayor and an Officer -- He Charges him with Distorting and Ingratimde. Committee Meetings. Bible Society Roceipts. Large Fire--Destruction of the New-haven and Harlem Railroad Freight Depot.

docs.lead_paragraph: Society Library--Blection of Trustees. Tuesday, April 29, being the day of the annual meeting of the shareholders of the New-York Society Library, the accordingly assembled at their new building in University-place. The meeting was called to order by Professor GEO, C. ANTHON, the Secretary, and Rev. SAMUEL OBOOD, D D., was called to the Chair.

docs.lead_paragraph: PERKINS INSTITUTION FOR THE BLIND.--The annual report of the Trustees of the perkins Institution transmitted to the Legislature. The cost of carrying on the establishment has greatly increased of late years, owing to an extension of its sphere of usefulness, and to the great increase in all expenses of living.
